It’s that time of the year again where getting school placement might be a headache. eNCA reporter Heidi Giokos is following that story. Courtesy of #DStv403  JOHANNESBURG - It might be back to school for most inland pupils on Wednesday, but this isn’t the case for all. Many parents are frustrated with district offices and schools across Gauteng. READ: Gauteng schools online application temporarily shut Some parents say they’ve been waiting for months for their children to be placed. With tensions brewing over the placement of some Grade 1 and 8 learners in Gauteng, Basic Education Minister Angie Motshekga has pleaded for patience. WATCH: Back to School | Race to place pupils "The department is aware that there are still learners who are yet to be placed in schools," she said. "At the moment, Gauteng is experiencing challenges in this regard and we appeal to parents and guardians to cooperate with the district officials to resolve any matter.”